      <h2>How They Actually Differ</h2>

      <h3>Workflow</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Browse integrated job board, select a job, AI automatically tailors your resume to match that specific job posting. Review the tailored version, approve, and apply—all in one platform.</p>
      <p><strong>ChatGPT:</strong> Provide your resume and job description, ask ChatGPT to tailor it, review the output, manually edit and format, then apply through external job sites. Multiple steps across different tools.</p>

      <h3>Automation vs Manual Effort</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> AI tailors resumes automatically when you select a job. You review each one (30-60 seconds) before applying. No prompts or manual editing required.</p>
      <p><strong>ChatGPT:</strong> Requires crafting effective prompts, providing job descriptions, reviewing output, and manually editing/formatting. More time-consuming and requires prompt engineering skills.</p>

      <h3>Output Quality</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Each resume is automatically optimized for ATS systems and matches job-specific keywords. Built with recruiter input and ATS validation. Consistent, professional formatting.</p>
      <p><strong>ChatGPT:</strong> Quality depends on your prompts and editing skills. May generate generic or inaccurate content. Requires manual verification and formatting. No built-in ATS optimization.</p>

      <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Simple setup—create profile, upload resume, start browsing. The platform handles tailoring automatically. No prompt engineering needed.</p>
      <p><strong>ChatGPT:</strong> Requires learning effective prompts, understanding resume best practices, and manual editing skills. Steeper learning curve for optimal results.</p>

      <h3>Friction Points</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Requires reviewing each tailored resume (adds 30-60 seconds per application). Free tier has credit limits for premium features.</p>
      <p><strong>ChatGPT:</strong> Manual process for each job—copy job description, craft prompt, review output, edit, format. No integrated job board or application tools. Requires separate tools for job search and tracking.</p>
